- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the interpretation of linear logic connectors and the existence of fixpoints, which are topics closely related to logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the interpretation of recursive algebraic datatypes, which is a topic in programming languages.
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with the interpretation of linear logic connectors, which are closely related to type theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the existence of fixpoints for particular functors, which is a topic in data structures.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the construction of finiteness spaces, which are used in some machine learning algorithms.
